get.description:
Return all active config issues for the operator.

Response shape::

    {
        "issues": [
            {
                "id": "hotel_missing_email",
                "severity": "error",
                "title": "Hotel has no booking email",
                "message": "'Grand Hotel' has no booking email ...",
                "target_route": "/settings/hotels"
            }
        ]
    }

Empty list means the operator has no active misconfigurations.
The dashboard renders nothing when issues is empty.

post.description:
Create a new operator-scoped tag.

The migration enforces:
  - per-operator name uniqueness (lower(name)) among active rows;
  - 1..64 char name length;
  - hex color format (#RRGGBB).

A duplicate-name violation surfaces as a 409.
